      <h2>Who This Is For</h2>

      <p>This is not a starter package. Done-for-you AI implementation is for businesses that:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Have real revenue</strong> and want to scale without adding proportional headcount</li>
        <li><strong>Are losing money to inefficiency</strong> — manual processes, slow follow-ups, missed leads, disjointed tools</li>
        <li><strong>Want a partner, not a vendor</strong> — someone who understands your operations and builds systems that actually fit</li>
        <li><strong>Need it done right the first time</strong> — no DIY trial and error, no half-built tools collecting dust</li>
        <li><strong>Operate at a scale where automation compounds</strong> — the more volume you do, the more every automated system saves</li>
      </ul>

      <p>We have scoped engagements from focused single-system builds to full-scale operational transformations spanning marketing, sales, operations, and client delivery. The scope matches your business — we do not sell you more than you need, and we do not build less than what will actually work.</p>

      <h2>What You Get That Others Do Not Offer</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Actual implementation, not just strategy.</strong> You get working systems, not a PowerPoint.</li>
        <li><strong>One partner for everything.</strong> Marketing, automation, AI, and technology — under one roof. No coordinating between five vendors.</li>
        <li><strong>Systems that work together.</strong> Your CRM talks to your email, which talks to your lead capture, which feeds your reporting. Everything is connected.</li>
        <li><strong>Ongoing management option.</strong> We do not build and disappear. Monthly retainers keep your systems optimized as your business evolves.</li>
        <li><strong>No technical knowledge required from you.</strong> We build it so your team can use it. If they can click a button, they can run the system.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What does done-for-you AI implementation actually include?</summary>
        <p>Everything. We audit your operations, identify where AI and automation will have the biggest impact, design the workflows, build and deploy the systems, train your team, and manage it ongoing. You do not need to know anything about AI — that is our job.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How much does this cost?</summary>
        <p>It depends entirely on the scope — the size of your business, the number of systems being automated, and the complexity of your operations. Engagements range from focused single-system builds to full-scale enterprise transformations. We scope and price every project individually after understanding your business. Book a consultation and we will give you an honest assessment.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How long does implementation take?</summary>
        <p>Focused projects — a single workflow or automation system — can go live in 2-4 weeks. Full-scale implementations involving multiple departments and systems typically take 1-3 months, rolled out in phases so you see value quickly without disrupting operations.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do I need technical staff to maintain this?</summary>
        <p>No. We build systems your existing team can use without technical knowledge. We also offer ongoing management retainers so we handle maintenance, updates, and optimization — you just use the systems.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How is this different from AI consulting?</summary>
        <p><a href="/services/ai-consulting/">AI consulting</a> gives you a strategy and roadmap. Done-for-you implementation builds and deploys the actual systems. We do both — but this service is for businesses that want the whole thing handled, not just advice.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can you work with our existing tools and software?</summary>
        <p>Yes. We integrate with the tools you already use — your CRM, email platform, scheduling software, payment systems, and more. If a better tool exists for the job, we will recommend it, but we do not force you onto new platforms unnecessarily.</p>
      </details>

